   =20
      Donations
   =20
 =20

Here=E2=80=99s a trade:
=09Start a company to, you know, invent teleportation or whatever.=09Write =
some financial projections about how much money you will make if you succee=
d, discount them by an optimistic estimate of your likelihood of success, a=
nd decide that your company is worth $1 billion.=09Donate 10% of the stock =
of your company to a nonprofit.=09Deduct the $100 million value of the dona=
tion on your taxes.=09Good work, now you never pay taxes again.
  [1]



To be clear, this is extremely not legal or tax advice. They are looking fo=
r this sort of thing! Anyway here=E2=80=99s=C2=A0a great story about a guy =
named Gregory Gerami, who came to Florida A&M University =E2=80=9Cto presen=
t a check for more than $237 million during the university=E2=80=99s May 4 =
graduation ceremony.=E2=80=9D I mean, a novelty check. Not a check. =E2=80=
=9CThe donation to FAMU was revealed to be private stocks in Gerami=E2=80=
=99s company, Batterson Farms Corp.=E2=80=9D And:

He=E2=80=99s maintained that his gift is worth around $237 million, though =
he admits no external valuation of the stocks has been conducted yet. =E2=
=80=A6=C2=A0
Officials have since admitted the stocks may be worthless. ...
Gerami told The Sun News Thursday he didn=E2=80=99t watch the meeting, and =
he feels all the criticism directed toward him is premature since there has=
n=E2=80=99t been any third-party valuation of the stock. His company is in =
the process of hiring a qualified appraiser, he said.
=E2=80=9CIf the valuation supports (the value we reported) of the gift, wha=
t will [critics] say?=E2=80=9D he asked.

Probably they=E2=80=99ll say =E2=80=9Cwhy doesn=E2=80=99t the school=C2=A0s=
ell the stock for $237 million then,=E2=80=9D would be my guess, but who kn=
ows.=C2=A0
Incidentally a reader once emailed me to suggest that Donald Trump could mo=
netize=C2=A0his Trump Media & Technology Group stock by donating it to his =
charitable foundation. At first I was skeptical, but he walked me through t=
he math and I was enlightened. The math is: What loan-to-value ratio=C2=A0w=
ould a bank give you in a non-recourse loan against a volatile meme stock y=
ou control? Because the IRS will give you 37%.

