 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the labor-relations a=
nd nutritional angles</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI had a guy come in with his family. =
It was a family of five. And he did 16 rounds of shrimp scampi,=E2=80=9D sa=
id James Berke, a 23-year-old in New Jersey, who until very recently worked=
 at a Red Lobster. =E2=80=9CHe was there for over two hours on a busy Frida=
y night. They had one of my biggest tables. I just had to watch this man ea=
t plates upon plates of the scampi, which isn=E2=80=99t even served over pa=
sta. It=E2=80=99s shrimp in a garlic-wine butter. It was so gross.=E2=80=9D=
 ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Berke=E2=80=99s experience serving a man who p=
ut away 16 servings over the course of two hours was actually mild compared=
 with some of the other stories I=E2=80=99ve heard. Josie, 19, who also ask=
ed to be anonymous, worked at a (now-shuttered) Kansas City Red Lobster, wh=
ere she watched a solo diner take down 30 orders of fried shrimp within fou=
r hours. According to the nutritional information on Red Lobster=E2=80=99s =
website, that=E2=80=99s something like 14,000 calories.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CHe was a skinny guy too,=E2=80=9D Jos=
ie said. =E2=80=9CI was like, <em>Where is it all going?</em>=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the top thing employees will not miss abou=
t Red Lobster are the arguments and confrontations they=E2=80=99d frequentl=
y endure when informing customers about the rules that come buoyed to the E=
ndless Shrimp deal. For instance, guests cannot request a box to take their=
 Endless Shrimp home, nor can they share their servings with the rest of th=
e table. (In other words, only one phantasmagoric shrimp binge per person.)=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CYou had groups coming in expecting to=
 feed their whole family with one order of endless shrimp,=E2=80=9D Josie s=
aid. =E2=80=9CI would get screamed at.=E2=80=9D She already had her share o=
f Cheddar Bay Biscuit battle stories, but the shrimp was something else: =
=E2=80=9CIt tops any customer service experience I=E2=80=99ve had. Some peo=
ple are just a different type of stupid, and they all wander into Red Lobst=
er.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What we discussed yesterday was the possibilit=
y =E2=80=94=C2=A0hinted at in Red Lobster=E2=80=99s bankruptcy papers =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0that the endless shrimp promotion was a way to funnel money fro=
m the failing Red Lobster to its controlling shareholder Thai Union Group P=
cl, which was also a big supplier. The theory is roughly that, as Red Lobst=
er slid into bankruptcy,=C2=A0Thai Union could not expect to get any value =
back=C2=A0<em>as a shareholder</em>; in fact, it <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35453198.258338/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJn=
LmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMjEvcmVkLWxvYnN0ZXItcy1zaHJpbXAtZGViYWN=
sZS1zcG90bGlnaHRzLTEtMi1iaWxsaW9uLXRoYWktZmFtaWx5P2NtcGlkPUJCRDA1MjEyNF9NT0=
5FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtP=
