nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the MoviePass economy</a>.=E2=80=9D T=
here, the theory was that venture capitalists wanted to fund businesses tha=
t were growing quickly and signing up lots of enthusiastic customers, witho=
ut particularly caring whether those businesses made money. Startups adapte=
d to those incentives: It is easier to grow quickly and impress your custom=
ers if you price your products way below cost, and so startups did. Sometim=
es this worked, and=C2=A0the startups quickly built big networks of dedicat=
ed customers and could rationalize their economics, and sometimes it didn=
=E2=80=99t.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the point was that, for a while, ordinary =
people=E2=80=99s lifestyles were <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/35453198.258338/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL25l=
